        About This Item

        We aim to show you accurate product information. Manufacturers, suppliers and others provide what you see here, and we have not verified it.
        Features

        Introducing a healthier way to fry, and so much more! That means it not only bakes, broils, and toasts, it also lets you air fry right inside the oven is a healthier way to prepare delicious fried favorites, from wings to fritters to fries to shrimp. And since toaster ovens stay on the countertop, this fryer doesn't have to move back and forth, from cupboard to counter. Enjoy the crunch without the calories and messy cleanup, with the Oven Fryer from Cuisinart!


        Cuisinart Toaster Oven Broilers Air Fryer:

        • Full-size toaster oven with a built-in air fryer
        • Healthier way to fry
        • Uses powerful ultra-hot air to air fry
        • 4-pound chicken requires only a teaspoon of oil to fry
        • 1800-Watt
        • 0.6 Cubic Foot Interior With Light
        • Nonstick Easy-Clean Interior
        • 60-Minute Timer/Auto Shutoff
        • Adjustable Thermostat
        • Convection Bake
        • Whisper Quiet Operation 
        • Includes: Oven Rack, Baking Pan, Air Fryer Rack/Basket 
        • 40oz. Olive Oil Spray Bottle
        • 4lb. Air Fry Capacity
        • Toast Shade Selector-Timer
        • Material: Stainless Steel
        7 Functions

        Average Rating:(4.0)out of 5 stars
        It takes practice
        I bought this to replace my broken toaster oven. The instructions that came with it will have you burning your food. We have had the most trouble when my son makes chicken tenders or pizza rolls. The temp needs to be much lower and the rack moved down. I will watch more videos from people who have it figured out. As an air fryer I haven't had any issues. Does a great job on that setting. The toast I'm still figuring out. It cleans fairly easily my only complaint is I wish it had a removable crumb tray in the bottom, it's hard to clean the crumbs out from under the coils. Definitely not regretting my purchase just need more time to figure it out.

        It takes practice

        January 31, 2021
        Verified purchase

        I bought this to replace my broken toaster oven. The instructions that came with it will have you burning your food. We have had the most trouble when my son makes chicken tenders or pizza rolls. The temp needs to be much lower and the rack moved down. I will watch more videos from people who have it figured out. As an air fryer I haven't had any issues. Does a great job on that setting. The toast I'm still figuring out. It cleans fairly easily my only complaint is I wish it had a removable crumb tray in the bottom, it's hard to clean the crumbs out from under the coils. Definitely not regretting my purchase just need more time to figure it out.

        My first air fryer

        May 4, 2021
        Verified purchase

        This is my first air fryer. Overall it's pretty cool. I had to read up on lowering the temp and shortening the cooking time b/c it cooks so quickly that it burns. I tried raw chicken breasts and the inside won't cook all the way through so I've had to cut in pieces which is a pain but my son loves nuggets....husband on the other hand would prefer otherwise. I'm learning the more we use it. The pan that the tray sits on is hard to clean and after about 10 uses is already stained...so I started using foil on the pan for anything that drips. The basket for air frying is also difficult to clean and will rust if you don't dry it completely. Don't walk away while it's cooking b/c you could have burnt food and not all recipes' cooking times will match with the Cuisinart's cooking time.

        Disappointed

        April 29, 2021
        Verified purchase

        My toaster oven died and I thought this would be a great replacement from the times it showed up on the "Best" lists. The first time I used it I burnt my dinner. It runs very hot and I have to lower the temp between 25 to 50 degrees. The temperature dial goes up to a broil setting but you can not turn it past 450. The timer starts at 10 minutes and if you need less you are better off setting and alternate timer. I had to broil something and the recipe said 1-2 minutes. I set it on the setting and turned the temp to 450 and it took over 10 minutes.
